President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Charles Keckler as a member of the Board of Directors of the Legal Services Corporation. Keckler is currently a member of the board and a Presidential Scholar at George Mason University's School of Public Policy. He has previously held positions at the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services and the George Mason University School of Law. Keckler holds degrees from Harvard College, the University of Michigan, and the University of Michigan Law School.